    clinicalRelevance: "Common laboratory chemical hazards: formalin/formaldehyde (carcinogen, fixative), xylene (flammable, neurotoxic, used in histology), methanol (toxic, flammable), acids (corrosive—hydrochloric, sulfuric), sodium azide (toxic preservative, forms explosive metal azides in drain pipes), mercury (toxic heavy metal, older thermometers).",
