    assessment: "SDS contains 16 sections: (1) identification, (2) hazard(s), (3) composition, (4) first-aid measures, (5) fire-fighting, (6) accidental release, (7) handling/storage, (8) exposure controls/PPE, (9) physical/chemical properties, (10) stability/reactivity, (11) toxicological information, (12) ecological, (13) disposal, (14) transport, (15) regulatory, (16) other information. Section 8 (PPE requirements) and Section 4 (first aid) are most critical for lab workers.",
